    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; DT, 9 and 10 Engine Service Manual - Variable Geometry Turbocharger
        (VGT) - Removal - Variable Geometry Turbocharger (VGT) Assembly and Turbocharger Oil Drain Tube
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="2">
        <title>Variable Geometry Turbocharger (VGT) Assembly and Turbocharger Oil Drain Tube</title>
        <step1>
            <para id="s0403" count="1">Loosen worm gear clamps on turbocharger air intake duct and breather tube. Pull
                turbocharger air intake duct off the VGT and crankcase breather assemblies.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen exhaust clamp and remove down pipe from VGT exhaust flange.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3350004123" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figk15/K15002.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Turbocharger oil drain tube, bracket, and bolt</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">M8 x 16 bolt</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Tube bracket (oil drain)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Turbocharger oil drain tube</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove M8 x 16 bolt from tube bracket and remove bracket.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Pull oil drain tube out of crankcase.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3350004124" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figk15/K15003.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>VGT mounting</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">M10 Spiralock&#174; nut (4)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Turbocharger mounting gasket</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">VGT mounting stud</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>To aid removal of the turbocharger, loosen four M10 nuts &#188; turn then tap each nut using a
                    socket or flat punch and a hammer. This will knock the "peaks" of the threads down, allowing the
                    nuts to unthread easily.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <warning>
                <para>To prevent personal injury or death, support turbocharger assembly during removal and
                    installation.
                </para>
            </warning>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove three of four M10 Spiralock&#174; nuts holding the VGT assembly to the exhaust
                manifold.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Support the VGT assembly and remove the fourth M10 nut. Remove the VGT assembly and oil
                drain tube.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove and discard the turbocharger mounting gasket and oil drain tube O-rings.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Discard used M10 Spiralock&#174; nuts.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
